sql:
SELECT region_name
FROM regions
WHERE average_consumption > (SELECT AVG(average_consumption) FROM regions);

external_knowledge:
- 'beacons' metaphorically represent KPI types which are indicators of performance;
- 'voyages of performance' is a poetic way to describe how KPI values are tracked over regions;
- 'sea of regions' symbolizes the different regions where performance is measured;
- 'average light of their stars' metaphorically refers to the average KPI value, where KPI values are likened to the brightness of stars.

